                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-131-off777 t18310217-131-crimeloc780"></join> - I sent two home, telling Hill the same man would be back for the third shortly; I saw the prisoner a few yards off, and have no doubt he heard this - I had occasionally employed the prisoner; I never received the butter.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-131-person1352">
                  JOSEPH 
                  HILL
               <interp inst="t18310217-131-person1352" type="surname" value="HILL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-131-person1352" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-131-person1352" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Evans bought three flats of butter of me, and sent two away by his porter - he said he would send for the third - the prisoner stood at Evans' elbow when he bought them, and must have heard what he said- in about five minutes the prisoner came and asked for the flat of butter; I delivered it to him, and did not see him again till next day, when he was in custody - I believed he was authorized to call for it; I am certain of his person - he had carried goods twice before for Mr. Gainsford.</p>


               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-131-person1353">
