                  </persName>
            . I am a patrol of Farringdon ward. I apprehended the prisoner on the 13th of February, and told him it was for the butter which he had from Hill's - he said he had sold it for 10d. a pound in Whitechapel-market, and threw the basket and cloths away.</p>
               <p>The prisoner pleaded distress.</p>
